<item>
            <title>[LU-2855] error management in KUC broadcast delivery</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2855</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;in KUC broadcast groups, the message delivery fails if a userland process terminates without closing its kuc channel properly.&lt;br/&gt;
This patch improves the behavior of KUC broadcast groups, to make it more adapted for HSM usage:&lt;br/&gt;
the message delivery is successful if at least 1 userland process is present in this group and receives the message successfully.&lt;br/&gt;
Only HSM copytools use KUC broadcast groups (no impact on changelog processing). &lt;/p&gt;</description>
